config.Messages.WinGoal: &fTo win you need to be the last one standing alive.

addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.basalt.description:
&7 A bit cooler place in
&7 hell where magma cubes
&7 wander and search
&7 for food.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.basalt.name: &f&l Basalt Deltas
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.beach.description:
&7 The best place for a vacation.
&7 Get some sunscreen and a
&7 good mood.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.beach.name: &f&l Beach
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.cherry_grove.description:
&7 A peaceful place filled
&7 with cherry blossoms,
&7 where spring never ends.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.cherry_grove.name: &f&l Cherry Grove
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.cold_fields.description:
&7 Cold and snowy place
&7 is not for everyone.
&7 But white foxes and
&7 rabbits have places
&7 where they hide.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.cold_fields.name: &f&l Snowy Taiga
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.cyan_forest.description:
&7 A safe place in an unsafe
&7 world.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.cyan_forest.name: &f&l Cyan Forest
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.deep_dark.description:
&7 Far underground, a
&7 place where the
&7 darkness is alive.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.deep_dark.name: &f&l Deep Dark
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.deep_frozen_ocean.description:
&7 A cold, deep ocean
&7 where icebergs float
&7 and polar bears roam.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.deep_frozen_ocean.name: &f&l Deep Frozen Ocean
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.desert.description:
&7 A hot wasteland with no
&7 water. Even rain does
&7 not fall here.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.desert.name: &f&l Desert
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.eroded_badlands.description:
&7 A land with its colors
&7 striped away by time,
&7 leaving beautiful cliffs.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.eroded_badlands.name: &f&l Eroded Badlands
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.fields.description:
&7 Flat but green, the best
&7 starting biome.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.fields.name: &f&l Plains
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.forest.description:
&7 A place where every
&7 bee would love to live.
&7 All the flowers that you
&7 wished for are here.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.forest.name: &f&l Flower Forest
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.frozen_peaks.description:
&7 Ice-capped mountains
&7 where the cold bites
&7 harder than anywhere.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.frozen_peaks.name: &f&l Frozen Peaks
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.frozen_river.description:
&7 A river frozen in time
&7 where only the bravest
&7 creatures can survive.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.frozen_river.name: &f&l Frozen River
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.frozen_water.description:
&7 A coldness of this
&7 ocean is matched
&7 only by its size.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.frozen_water.name: &f&l Cold Ocean
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.grove.description:
&7 A quiet, snowy forest
&7 where the trees stand
&7 tall and silent.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.grove.name: &f&l Grove
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.hell.description:
&7 Not a place where
&7 living things should wander.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.hell.name: &f&l Hell
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.ice_spikes.description:
&7 Towers of ice rising
&7 from the frozen land,
&7 where nothing grows.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.ice_spikes.name: &f&l Ice Spikes
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.jagged_peaks.description:
&7 Dangerous mountains
&7 with sharp cliffs that
&7 few dare to climb.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.jagged_peaks.name: &f&l Jagged Peaks
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.jungle.description:
&7 Hard to navigate and
&7 a rainy place.
&7 Ideal for ocelots.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.jungle.name: &f&l Jungle
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.lost_souls.description:
&7 Those who stay here too long
&7 may get stuck and never be
&7 able to leave.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.lost_souls.name: &f&l Lost Soul Valley
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.mooshroom.description:
&7 Mycelium infested blocks
&7 spread faster than
&7 grass and infest everything
&7 in their way. Almost nothing
&7 can survive here.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.mooshroom.name: &f&l Infested Land
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.mountain.description:
&7 A dangerous place where
&7 only crazy goats can
&7 survive.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.mountain.name: &f&l Mountain Slopes
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.mushroom_fields.description:
&7 A strange place where
&7 mushrooms grow tall
&7 and cows are red.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.mushroom_fields.name: &f&l Mushroom Fields
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.old_growth_pine_taiga.description:
&7 An ancient forest of
&7 towering pines where
&7 few dare to tread.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.old_growth_pine_taiga.name: &f&l Old Growth Pine Taiga
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.pretty_caves.description:
&7 Deep underground are still
&7 some places with greenery.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.pretty_caves.name: &f&l Lush Caves
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.red_forest.description:
&7 Even in hell you
&7 can find some places
&7 where life survives.
&7 Be aware of angry pigs.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.red_forest.name: &f&l Red Forest
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.savanna.description:
&7 A warm and almost dry
&7 place with rapid rains.
&7 Only acacia trees can
&7 survive there.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.savanna.name: &f&l Savanna
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.simple_ocean.description:
&7 A deep dark ocean may
&7 provide some cod,
&7 but squids may wander
&7 in its depth.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.simple_ocean.name: &f&l Deep Ocean
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.snowy_slopes.description:
&7 Steep snowy slopes
&7 where goats roam
&7 and avalanches fall.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.snowy_slopes.name: &f&l Snowy Slopes
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.sparse_jungle.description:
&7 A lightly wooded area
&7 where jungle meets
&7 open plains.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.sparse_jungle.name: &f&l Sparse Jungle
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.stony_shore.description:
&7 The rocky coastline
&7 is not a soft place
&7 but offers hidden gems.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.stony_shore.name: &f&l Stony Shore
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.sunflower_plains.description:
&7 A beautiful open field
&7 where sunflowers
&7 turn to follow the sun.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.sunflower_plains.name: &f&l Sunflower Plains
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.swamp.description:
&7 A sticky place where
&7 you should not want
&7 to stay.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.swamp.name: &f&l Swamp
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.taiga.description:
&7 Cold but not snowy
&7 forest. Rabbits and
&7 foxes love this
&7 weather.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.taiga.name: &f&l Taiga
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.warm_ocean.description:
&7 A warm ocean is
&7 ideal for swimming,
&7 and catching some
&7 colorful fish.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.warm_ocean.name: &f&l Warm Ocean
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.windswept_forest.description:
&7 A forest battered by
&7 strong winds, only the
&7 toughest trees survive.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.windswept_forest.name: &f&l Windswept Forest
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.windswept_savanna.description:
&7 Dry and cracked lands
&7 where strong winds
&7 blow through the grass.
addons/Biomes/biomesTemplate.biomes.windswept_savanna.name: &f&l Windswept Savanna

addons/CauldronWitchery/books/first_grim.first_grimoire.author: &d Unknown
addons/CauldronWitchery/books/first_grim.first_grimoire.pages.0:
&5 Foreword: Dear reader this book
is intended to pass on my knowledge.
Feeling the need to discover the
arts of magic, I do not suggest
to perform these experiments.
addons/CauldronWitchery/books/first_grim.first_grimoire.pages.1:
Warnings:
Do not stand too close to the cauldron
as some magic is not stable, but they
may produce the best outcome.
addons/CauldronWitchery/books/first_grim.first_grimoire.pages.2:
I have encountered times where I've felt
dumbfounded of the missing requirements
to my experiment which caused my
knowledge to decrease.
PLEASE REMEMBER THE EXTRA INGREDIENTS.
addons/CauldronWitchery/books/first_grim.first_grimoire.pages.3:
By using my magic stick on the cauldron
and holding the key ingredient in my left
hand... I manage to combine the ingredients
in something new...
addons/CauldronWitchery/books/first_grim.first_grimoire.pages.4:
Here are the combinations of elements
that I manage to produce.
addons/CauldronWitchery/books/first_grim.first_grimoire.pages.last:
In the Second Grimoire book you will
find more recipes, but they require
better magic stick, otherwise the
outcome may explode.
addons/CauldronWitchery/books/first_grim.first_grimoire.recipe.book-header:
&r&2&l [book]
&r&l Key ingredient: &r [offhand]
&r A [cauldron_level] &n [cauldron] &r and
&r&n [level] &r parts Knowledge!
addons/CauldronWitchery/books/first_grim.first_grimoire.recipe.item-header:
&2&l [item]
&r&l Key ingredient: &r [offhand]
&r A [cauldron_level] &n [cauldron] &r and
&r&n [level] &r parts Knowledge!
addons/CauldronWitchery/books/first_grim.first_grimoire.recipe.mob-header:
&2&l [mob]
&r&l Key ingredient: &r [offhand]
&r A [cauldron_level] &n [cauldron] &r and
&r&n [level] &r parts Knowledge!
addons/CauldronWitchery/books/first_grim.first_grimoire.title: First Grimoire

addons/CauldronWitchery/books/first_grim.first_grimoire.author: &d Nezināms
addons/CauldronWitchery/books/first_grim.first_grimoire.pages.0:
&5 Esi brīdināts: šī grāmata satur
visus manas dzīves laikā veiktos
eksperimentus. Ar savu burvju
nūjiņu esmu atklājis daudz receptes
taču tās var izrādīties bīstamas.
addons/CauldronWitchery/books/first_grim.first_grimoire.pages.1:
Uzmanību:
Nestāvi pārāk tuvu katlam. Maģija
var padarīt to nestabilu un tas
var uzsprāgt.
addons/CauldronWitchery/books/first_grim.first_grimoire.pages.2:
Esmu daudzkārt bijis neuzmanīgs
veicot šos maģiskos rituālus un
aizmirsis ingredientus.
Esi uzmanīgs un pārliecinies, ka
tev ir visi ingredienti.
addons/CauldronWitchery/books/first_grim.first_grimoire.pages.3:
Turot labajā rokā burvju nūjiņu un
kreisajā galveno ingredientu, ar
labo klikšķi uzspied uz katla.
addons/CauldronWitchery/books/first_grim.first_grimoire.pages.4:
Tālāk sekos saraksts ar dažām receptēm,
ko man izdevās atklāt.
addons/CauldronWitchery/books/first_grim.first_grimoire.pages.last:
Otrajā sējumā es aprakstīju
maģiskos rituālus, ko veicu ar
labāku burvju nūjiņu.
addons/CauldronWitchery/books/first_grim.first_grimoire.title: Pirmais Sējums

addons/CauldronWitchery/books/second_gri.second_grimoire.author: &d Unknown
addons/CauldronWitchery/books/second_gri.second_grimoire.pages.0:
Foreword: If you have read my previous books,
you should know the standard procedures and
safety precautions. I would like to say from
this point onwards... These magic can cause
death and destruction.

addons/CauldronWitchery/books/second_gri.second_grimoire.author: &d Nezināms
addons/CauldronWitchery/books/second_gri.second_grimoire.pages.0:
Ja esi lasījis iepriekšējo grāmatu,
tad jau zināsi par esošajiem ietiekumiem.
Atceries, ka maģija mēdz būt nestabila.
addons/CauldronWitchery/books/second_gri.second_grimoire.title: Otrais Sējums

config.playerGuide:
&2&lPlayer's Guidebook&0: &2Basic Mechanics:&0 In this game your goal is to stop the enemies before they reach the red section of the map. Every enemy that manages to reach the red section of the map deducts one life from your life pool. You have 20 lives in total.
All enemies spawn at the green section of the map. You can build towers to stop the enemies and make mazes with the towers to slow them down.
Enemies attack in waves. As you progress through the game, the waves will increase in difficulty. There is a 10 second cool-down between every wave.
Basic towers are the only towers in the game that do damage. You can modify how basic towers function and what they do by placing support towers right next the to them.
Any tower that you place down will block enemies. Enemies DO NOT move through squares diagonally. So keep that in mind when placing down towers.
As you kill enemies they will drop gold. You can use gold to buy more towers. If you manage to go through a wave without loosing any lives you will be rewarded with some bonus gold for your efforts. You start out with 150 gold.
&6Tools - Upgrade:&0 You can use this tool to upgrade a tower and increase its stats such as, firing speed, damage, and so on.
&6Tools - Sell:&0 Use the sell tool to remove a tower. You will gain back some gold from selling a tower, but it will not be the full amount you paid when you first purchased the tower.
&6Tools - Next Wave:&0 This tool allows you to skip the 10 second cooldown between waves.
&dTowers - Basic:&0 The only towers in the entire game that do any damage. There is not much to them. Put them down and when an enemy is near, they will shoot an arrow at it. Upgrade the tower to double its damage and increase its firing speed.
&dTowers - Barricade:&0 This tower does nothing but block. If you need to build a maze on the cheap, then this is the tower for you.
&dTowers - Sugar:&0 When this support tower is placed near a basic tower it will increase its firing speed. Upgrade it to increase its effect.
&dTowers - Spyglass:&0 When this support tower is placed near a basic tower it will increase its range. Upgrade it to increase its effect.
&dTowers - Beam &dGenerator:&0 When this support tower is placed near a basic tower it will transform the basic tower into a beam tower. Beam towers take a while to warm up and start doing maximum damage. Upgrade it to increase its effect.
&dTowers - Explosion &dFactory:&0 When this support tower is placed near a basic tower it will transform the tower into an explosive tower. The tower will now be able to damage enemies in a radius. Upgrade it to increase its effect.
&dTowers - Ice Box:&0 When this support tower is placed near a basic tower it will give the tower a slow effect. Any enemies hit by the tower will be slowed down. Upgrade it to increase its slow duration and power.
&dTowers - Armor &dCrusher:&0 When this support tower is placed near a basic tower it will gain the armor crush effect which will damage the enemies armor. Upgrade it to increase its effect.
&dTowers - Gold Mine:&0 When this support tower is placed near a basic tower, you will gain extra gold from any kills it makes. Upgrade it to increase its effect.
&dTowers - Obsidian &dQuarry:&0 When this support tower is placed near a basic tower it will give the tower a chance to score a critical hit. Critical hits will do 1.5X damage to the enemy. Upgrade it to increase its critical chance.
&dTowers - Napalm Dispenser:&0 When this support tower is placed near a basic tower it will allow the tower to set enemies on fire. 10% of the tower damage will be dealt as damage over time to the enemy.
&9Wave property - Air:&0 A player should know that Air waves consist of flying enemies that ignore any paths and just fly over your towers. Best to deal with them quickly!
&9Wave property - &9Horde:&0 Just when you thought a normal wave had a lot to throw at you, the Horde wave comes along to double the fun. You want lots of explosives to stop the Horde!
&9Wave property - &9Fast:&0 Have you heard of those Fast waves? They're so quick. Ensure their pace is slowed down, or it'll be game over before you can blink.
&9Wave property - &9Resist:&0 If you see a Resist wave coming up. You better be ready because that wave stops for nothing. Not even ice can can slow them down.
&9Wave property - &9Treasure:&0 The best wave property! Enemies with this property will drop extra gold when killed. It's payday!
&9Wave property - &9Boss:&0 And of course the dreaded Boss wave. Tough and loaded with health. Taking these down will not be easy. But I will tell you a secret. Every Boss hates the beam.
I am sure you have learned a lot, but did you know that waves can have multiple properties. That's right! Waves can be, Fast Resist, Boss Air Fast, or any combination you can think of. Ugh, just thinking about Fast Horde waves makes me shiver.
Before you head out there to become the greatest EternalTD player you can be. I want to share with you some basic tower building tips and strats.
When building explosive towers it can be a great idea to throw in some ice box or obsidian quarry support towers in the mix to give the explosive towers some extra edge.
If you want to build beam towers that can melt anything that comes near them. Then I recommend you make a single tower and surround it with spyglass, sugar, and beam support towers.
Do not be afraid to experiment and come up with your own builds and strats! Sometimes even just building masses of regular towers and backing them up with beam tower builds can get you pretty far!
Oh! I almost forgot! As you defeat more and more waves. You will start seeing waves that will start spawning splitterlings. And then waves where splitterlings spawn more splitterlings. Splitterlings do not drop any gold.
If you have read this far then you are ready to play. See you on the scoreboard!

levelDescription: &aI heard you need H2O to live.

message: &aWelcome to EternalTD! This guide will introduce the basic mechanics of this game.
&aStart by placing &6Basic Towers&a in the locations highlighted with &2green concrete&a blocks and &cred arrows&a!
&aYou can place a tower by selecting the correct item in the hotbar and right clicking on the floor tile with it, even from far away!
&aLet's step it up! &6Barricades do not deal damage, and are cheap to place, which makes them an amazing mazing tool!
&aPlace &6Basic Towers&a on &2green concrete blocks &aand &6Barricades &aon &6brown concrete blocks&a!
&aLet's try out support towers! Open your inventory and put a &fSugar Tower&a and an &9Ice Box&a tower in your hotbar!
&aSupport towers don't do any damage on their own, and are used to improve your &6Basic Towers&a!
&aPlace the &fSugar Towers&a on the &fwhite concrete blocks&a and the &9Ice Box&a towers on the &9blue concrete blocks!
&aLet's learn about tower combinations! Some support towers are always handy to have, like &bSpyglass Towers&a!
&aPlacing a &bSpyglass Tower&a next to a &6Basic Tower&a will extend the range of the &6Basic Tower&a.
&aPlace &bSpyglass Towers&a on the &bcyan concrete blocks&a and &cExplosion Factories&a on &cred concrete blocks&a!
&aSupport towers are pretty cool, but upgrading &6Basic Towers&a has its advantages too!
&aUsing the upgrade tool let's upgrade the &aBasic Towers&a on the &2green concrete&a tiles indicated by the &cred arrows&a!
&aTime to make a monolithic tower! These are towers that have one &6Basic Tower&a in the middle, and are surrounded entirely by support towers!
&aWe're going to have to make some space here so you will have to sell some of your &6Basic Towers&a using the sell tool!

&aBuild the following: a &6Basic Tower&a on &2green concrete&a, &bSpyglass Towers&a on &bcyan concrete&a, a &eGold Mine&a on &6orange concrete&a, a &7Obsidian Quarry&a on &5purple concrete&a, a &7Armor Crusher&a tower on &7gray concrete&a and a &3Beam Generator&a on &eyellow concrete&a.
&aAnd now let's make the opposite! In the opposite design of a monolith you have a design where there is a support tower in the middle and you surround it with &6Basic Towers&a!
&aBuild the following: &6Basic Towers&a on &2green concrete&a, &cExplosion Factories&a on &cred concrete&a and &9Ice Box&a towers on &9blue concrete&a.
&6You are now ready to build however you want! &aDo you want to upgrade existing towers, build new towers or even tweak the design of the maze? The choice is yours!
&cThis is the end of the building tutorial, you have 15s before the next wave begins! &aOne last tip. You can build, upgrade, and sell towers during game-play!
&4Warning! The next wave is an air wave, which means the mobs will fly over your towers!

&aAs you can see, &6Basic Towers&a shoot arrows! &6Basic Towers&a are the only towers that deal damage, all other towers are made to support them and should be placed around the &6Basic Towers&a, except for the &6Barricades&a which we will take a look at in a bit.
&aNow mobs can't go through the tiles you blocked with the &6Barricades&a, and are forced to cross the bridge to get to the end (the red area)!
&aAs you can see on indicated on top of the &6Basic Towers&a, &fSugar Towers&a increase the attack speed of &6Basic Towers&a and &9Ice Box&a towers add a slowness effect to the &6Basic Towers&a!
&aThese effects stack based on the upgrade level of the support towers and their amount. And there is no hard limit!
cExplosion Factories&a add an area of effect to your &6Basic Towers&a making them an excellent choice for dealing with hordes of enemies!
&aThere are many interesting combinations you can achieve between support towers! I recommend you try it out in a few waves when you can free build.
&aUpgrading towers doubles some of their stats! A towers stats are always displayed right above it.

&aBeam monoliths like the one you built are perfect for melting bosses! Wave 10 is a boss wave, so you will soon be able to see the &3Beam Tower&a in action. However, beams are not great against large groups, as they take 3 seconds (upgradable) to reach max damage!
&aThere is no best or worst tower in ETD, a healthy mix of different tower combinations placed wisely is what leads you to victory!
&aThis is a &6Treasure Wave&a! Some waves have special attributes, such as fast, boss, treasure, resistant, and more. Be ready for anything!
&4This is a air wave, which means that the mobs will fly to their destination!
