guide.Entries.Assembling Devices.Description: Now that you have the required resources to get the bare minamum, craft a crude assembler by hand, once you have that crafted, you can use it to craft a power pylon, 2 combustion generators and a basic assembler. The Crude Assembler is the only hand crafted item in Minetorio!
guide.Entries.Auto Miner.Description: An auto miner is a powerful device. On its own it isn't very useful. You’ll need to support its output. Crushing all of its stone down into sand is useful with sifters for getting early iron and gold. Stone is also needed to make movers for logistic science packs.
guide.Entries.Automated Storage.Description: Movers can create automated storage systems. Their internal inventory acts as a filter. You can switch between allow and deny lists by right-clicking the mover with a wire tool.
guide.Entries.Automation Science Packs.Descrip: With these devices you can now craft Automation Science Packs at a basic assembler and then research some technology in the research lab!
guide.Entries.Automation.Description: This might sound obvious, but automation is very important for progressing at a reasonable rate. If you're stuck, look for tasks you can automate like crafting, moving items, or traveling. Sometimes slowing down speeds you up.
guide.Entries.BAAA!.Description: A nice early-game factory is an auto carpet crafting factory. You just need an auto shearer near some sheep, move the wool into a crafter to make carpet, and then move the carpet into a chest using a mover. You’ll need to occasionally supply shears.
guide.Entries.Biter Nests.Description: Biter nests absorb pollution and convert it into biters. If pollution stops reaching them, they will eventually stop spawning new biters and attacking. Over time, active nests evolve and produce stronger biters.
guide.Entries.Biters!.Description: Once you are creating enough pollution you are going to attract the natives! Make sure to build defenses or reduce your pollution! The more pollution you make the more biters will come!
guide.Entries.Colored Belts.Description: Belts of different colors won’t merge. You can place them side-by-side and keep them separate for clean logistics.
guide.Entries.Deep Drills.Description: Deep drills are mid-game miners. They require a lot of tech to work properly and use lubricant. They are ideal for extracting large amounts of a specific resource like iron or copper.
guide.Entries.Devices Strong Together.Descript: Most devices do one simple thing. On their own, they aren’t much, but combined with others they form complex and powerful factories.
guide.Entries.First Automation.Description: You can automate something easily right off the bat! Movers! They just take stone and furnaces. Take the time to setup a small mover factory. Use furnaces to smelt stone once, and then move it using movers to smelt it again. Then use a crafter to create movers automatically! Even if you have to hand feed the setup coal and cobblestone it will save you alot of time!
guide.Entries.Fuel Alternatives.Description: After getting logistics unlocked you gain access to a bit of tech. You could automate a tree farm to produce charcoal for steam power, or you could gather kelp blocks for power too. Steam power is critical for the power usage you will need for any sizeable factory and it really isn't to hard to get too.
guide.Entries.Gathering Supplies.Description: The first thing you should do when getting started is gather resources. Over gathering is a great idea! Gather 1 stack of each at least, iron, copper & smooth stone. Youll need 3 glass and 2 furnaces as well. Also you can mark these as done whenever you want by clicking this!
guide.Entries.Grabbers.Description: Movers that have their back face towards a belt will grab off that belt if it is motorized and has items on the belt. It will grab from whichever side is closer unless both sides of the belt face into the mover. Movers in this setup are called grabbers. Grabbers with levers above them will grab from both sides regardless of which side is closer.
guide.Entries.Industrial Components.Descriptio: Automate the production of iron gear wheels, iron plates, copper plates, and copper cables. These are used in nearly every mid-to-late-game device. Try splitting copper and iron production instead of crafting everything in a single assembler.
guide.Entries.Inserters.Description: Movers that have their face towards a belt are called inserters if they are not motorized. The belts will insert their item onto the belt if there isn't an item there already. It can only insert into the side of the belt that is closer. However, you can use a lever above this to allow it to insert onto both sides.
guide.Entries.Limit Bypass Mover.Description: This mover bypasses item limits in containers and devices when it has a button above it. Useful for using barrels like chests in Minetorio.
guide.Entries.Logistic Robots!.Description: Logistic robots require provider chests, requester chests, and a roboport. Robots are stored in roboports and operate within the power grid. Provider chests send items, requester chests pull items, and the robots do the transferring automatically.
guide.Entries.Logistics.Description: Once you unlock logistics alot of technology will become available for research. A great goal after having mover automation setup is to work on a better power source. Steam power is very important, you will need alot of fuel for this though. You can invest heavily into solar if you want but you will need alot of batteries and good weather for it to work at scale.
guide.Entries.Major Milestone.Description: Automated steam power is a major milestone. Your now ready to go for some really big technologies. You will need to make factories to automate Automation Science Packs and Logistic Science Packs to get some of the better techs, as their costs are becoming steep.
guide.Entries.Motorized Movers.Description: Movers with repeaters above them are motorized, so all of the connected carpet from their front face will move items like a conveyor belt. NEVER have two motorized movers using the same belts. The belt will not work and will behave wildly!
guide.Entries.Mover Lift.Description: Movers facing straight up or down can use fences to create a vertical lift. Lifts move items vertically like belts, and movers can interact with any part of them.
guide.Entries.Movers Tips.Description: You can quickly invert a mover by hitting 'F' while looking at it. Use a wire tool to toggle between whitelist and blacklist mode.
guide.Entries.Movers.Description: Movers are super important, they can move items from containers like chests and furnaces, to belts and other devices. Carpet is used as a belt, having a sheep farm is actually pretty important.
guide.Entries.Need for Speed.Description: Smooth stone and concrete increase player movement speed. While the boost is small, it saves time in large factories. Consider building pathways—concrete is twice as fast as smooth stone!
guide.Entries.Oil Processing.Description: Oil is quite a process, but when completed you get access to insane power—great for late game. You will need multiple oil refineries to break oil down into petrol. Heavy oil becomes light oil, light oil becomes petrol. Petrol is used in petroleum engines for lots of power, and also for crafting plastic bars—vital for red circuits.
guide.Entries.Overdriving.Description: You can overdrive motorized movers by placing an overdriver facing them. Up to 3 overdrivers will boost a mover to 4× speed. Other devices like auto miners can also be overdriven for increased speed.
guide.Entries.Overflow Mover.Description: This type of mover only outputs items when its input is full. It works for containers with more than one input slot. Create it by placing a comparator above a mover!
guide.Entries.Phase Belts.Description: Place a stair facing a belt end, then another stair facing the opposite direction in line with it. Items will *enter* the first stair and *exit* the second one using the belt in front. Great for creative transport setups.
guide.Entries.Pollution Map.Description: You can view pollution levels around you by using /mt map. This will also show nearby biter nests!
guide.Entries.Power Alternatives.Description: You could invest into solar power, you will need very little automation science for it. It would also be wise to research batteries to as solar on it's own suffers from night time and from daily cloud forecast. And they need to be cleared of debris every so often.
guide.Entries.Power Grids.Description: Most devices need a power grid to draw power from! The power pylon create a power grid! But the power pylon doesn't make power! You need a power generator to make power for your power grid! This is why we crafted combustion generators! They can provide power to the power grid! Power grids from power pylons are not huge. But you can link power pylons together to create a larger power grid!
guide.Entries.Power Pylons.Description: Power pylons are critical to expanding your power grid in. They are very cheap to make, they can also give some in depth information about your connected power grid. Like the amount of power being made and consumed!
guide.Entries.Quick Insert & Take.Description: Left-click a device to take its output. Sneak + right-click to insert 1 or 10% of what you're holding into the input slot. Works with furnaces, blast furnaces, and smokers.
guide.Entries.Ratios.Description: A lot of devices when used together have ratios at which they can work in harmony together. For example, a water pump can produce up to 100 water per action which happens in 3 seconds—so 33 water per second. A boiler uses 30 water per action, which is in 1 second. Therefore 1 water pump is needed per boiler. But you may have noticed the 3 leftover water. At a small scale this ratio works, but at a larger scale you could reduce the pumps slightly and be more efficient.
guide.Entries.Recipe Copy & Paste.Description: You can copy a recipe from an assembler by sneak + swap key. Then paste it into another assembler using the swap key.
guide.Entries.Repeaters.Description: Motorized movers can have a repeater above them. By default with delay 0, the mover will insert items onto both sides of the belt. You can control direction by changing the delay, or alternate sides by using delay 4.
guide.Entries.Research Tips.Description: You are going to need alot of resources to tech up, take the time to setup automation, otherwise you will be hand crafting alot and moving alot by hand.
guide.Entries.Research.Description: Science packs are important to progressing your technology. It is unlocked by converting science packs into tech progression. Once you hit 100% progression you unlock that tech. You can only progress research if you have 1 of each required science pack in the research labs!
guide.Entries.Resource Zone Chances.Descriptio: Iron zones are commonly found in cold biomes. But seismic charges can create resource zones even in caves or unexpected biomes. Copper is common in savannas and plains but can appear anywhere. Gold and redstone are only found underground, but redstone can be extracted by surface drills. Coal is most common in swamps, but forests have an okay chance too.
guide.Entries.Resource Zones.Description: Resource zones are created using a seismic charge in an unscanned chunk. They contain large amounts of raw resources and are essential for mass production. Resource zones have minimum spacing and can be depleted. Use trains to transport the output.
guide.Entries.Steam Power 1.Description: Steam power uses a few things to work. First you will need a pump, a boiler and 3 steam engines, along with 6 grindstones. You will also need a material like granite, andesite or diorite. These blocks are used as pipes. First you will need a pump setup over some water.
guide.Entries.Steam Power 2.Description: Make sure to place a andesite wall above the pump. Then make a connection of walls all the way to your boiler. You will need a polished andesite block to act as a junction, this allows liquids to enter devices connected to the polished blocks. Make sure to fuel the boiler, now it will convert water into steam!
guide.Entries.Steam Power 3.Description: With the steam you will need to make a pipe connection from the boiler to 3 steam engines. Do it the same way you did for the pump connection! Once steam reaches the steam engines they will begin producing loads of power! You will need to place 2 grindstones on each steam engine so it can vent the steam properly otherwise it's power output is reduced.
guide.Entries.The Pipe Tool.Description: Use the pipe tool to view a liquid path by clicking a device like a pump, boiler, or refinery. Paths are shown repeatedly while holding the tool. Liquid pipes are limited to 100 connected segments.
guide.Entries.Trains!.Description: Train stations are the holy grail of item transport. Use them to move stacks of items from faraway places. Rather than building factories on resource sites, train the resources into a centralized processing factory.
guide.Entries.Wire Tool Tips.Description: The wire tool can sort your own inventory with the swap button (F by default). Sneak + right-click a chest to sort it instantly!
guide.Entries.Wire Tool.Description: A wiretool is very important, it can show your power grid so you can see how far your power reaches. It also lets you see your power usage at a glance by simply looking at a device.

items.Devices.Advanced Assembler.Description: Attempts to craft the selected item. Uses resources from its input slots to craft. It will output crafted items into its output slots. Can use liquids in its crafting recipes.
items.Devices.Advanced Assembler.Name: Advanced Assembler
items.Devices.Advanced Bow Turret.Description: Requires and autobow and arrows to shoot. Useful for defending from mobs and biters.
items.Devices.Advanced Bow Turret.Name: Advanced Bow Turret
items.Devices.Artillery Device.Description: Can shoot artillery shells up to 500 blocks away using artillery beacons. Shoots 3 shells in one volley!
items.Devices.Artillery Device.Name: Artillery Device
items.Devices.Asteroid Collector.Description: Uses to gather asteroid chunks. Requires iron pickaxes or better to operate! This will always face north when placed.
items.Devices.Asteroid Collector.Name: Asteroid Collector
items.Devices.Atlas.Description: This is used to control a spaceship. It can be used to tell a ship to travel to specific coordinates above a planet or to travel to another planet.
items.Devices.Atlas.Name: Atlas
items.Devices.Atmospheric Controller.Descripti: Stabilizes a 100 block volume of space. Emits oxygen using gas cansiters with oxygen. This will also use power to produce heat. The space must be enclosed! Emissions occur from the top of the device!
items.Devices.Atmospheric Controller.Name: Atmospheric Controller
items.Devices.Auto Breaker.Description: This will break whatever block is in front of it. It uses pickaxes to operate. This requires the chunk to be loaded to work.
items.Devices.Auto Breaker.Name: Auto Breaker
items.Devices.Auto Breeder.Description: This will feed nearby animals foor for them to breed. This requires wheat or seeds to work. And this only works while the chunk is loaded.
items.Devices.Auto Breeder.Name: Auto Breeder
items.Devices.Auto Butcher.Description: This will kill nearby animals if there is 8 or more of the same type nearby. This requires swords to work and also only works while the chunk is loaded.
items.Devices.Auto Butcher.Name: Auto Butcher
items.Devices.Auto Cauldron.Description: Will fill empty buckets with filled liquid from the cauldron once it is full!
items.Devices.Auto Cauldron.Name: Auto Cauldron
items.Devices.Auto Collector.Description: Will collect dropped items within a configurable range. Inputs are used to restrict the items the dropper will pickup.
items.Devices.Auto Collector.Name: Auto Collector
items.Devices.Auto Duster.Description: Cleans debris off of solar panels. This will output sand after sometime. The range is limited to a 3x3 area.
items.Devices.Auto Duster.Name: Auto Duster
items.Devices.Auto Harvester.Description: This can harvest various crops, it will use hoes to do so. It also requires the chunk to be loaded in order to harvest.
items.Devices.Auto Harvester.Name: Auto Harvester
items.Devices.Auto Logger.Description: This uses axes to break logs in a large area. The logs are placed into the devices output slots.
items.Devices.Auto Logger.Name: Auto Logger
items.Devices.Auto Milker.Description: Will milk nearby cows using buckets. This will output milk buckets into its output slots. This only works while the chunk is loaded.
items.Devices.Auto Milker.Name: Auto Milker
items.Devices.Auto Miner.Description: Will mine blocks underneath it in a configurable range. Requires pickaxes in the input slots to work. You need to use at least iron picks for this to mine all resources.
items.Devices.Auto Miner.Name: Auto Miner
items.Devices.Auto Placer.Description: This will place blocks in a cube in front of it. The square size is defined by its inputs. It will place on air only, and will never replace a block. All dimensions are capped to 32. This only works if the chunk is loaded. This cannot place devices.
items.Devices.Auto Placer.Name: Auto Placer
items.Devices.Auto Planter.Description: This will plant saplings in a 3 block radius. It will plant seeds in an 11x11x3 area. It can also bonemeal saplings and seeds!
items.Devices.Auto Planter.Name: Auto Planter
items.Devices.Auto Plucker.Description: This will pluck feathers from nearby chickens! Each chicken can be plucked every 30 seconds. And this only works while the chunk is loaded.
items.Devices.Auto Plucker.Name: Auto Plucker
items.Devices.Auto Shearer.Description: This will shear any nearby sheep! This requires shears to work! This will only work while the chunk is loaded.
items.Devices.Auto Shearer.Name: Auto Shearer
items.Devices.Auto Timer.Description: Pulses adjacent observers when the timer hits zero. Timer is based on the amount of items in input slots. Minimum time is 1 second and this only works when the chunk is loaded.
items.Devices.Auto Timer.Name: Auto Timer
items.Devices.Barrel Pump.Description: When placing a filled liquid barrel in this devices input slots it will empty the liquid and place the emptied barrel into its output slots. If the barrel is empty in an input slot, then it will fill the barrel and output it.
items.Devices.Barrel Pump.Name: Barrel Pump
items.Devices.Basic Assembler.Description: Attempts to craft the selected item. Uses resources from its input slots to craft. It will output crafted items into its output slots.
items.Devices.Basic Assembler.Name: Basic Assembler
items.Devices.Battery Monitor.Description: This can be linked to other devices using the wire tool. Then it can be configured to turn devices on or off at certain battery levels.
items.Devices.Battery Monitor.Name: Battery Monitor
items.Devices.Battery.Description: Stores access power from the power grid. It can release power back into the grid when needed.
items.Devices.Battery.Name: Battery
items.Devices.Biter Detector.Description: This device will send a warning for incoming biter attacks. You might need multiple of these for larger factories.
items.Devices.Biter Detector.Name: Biter Detector
items.Devices.Blueprinter.Description: This can create user schematics. Ehich can be placed using this as well. Schematics are placed as blocks are provided to its input slots.
items.Devices.Blueprinter.Name: Blueprinter
items.Devices.Boiler.Description: Uses water and burns fuel to create steam. Fuel burns twice as along compared to vanilla. Water needs to be piped in using liquid pipes.
items.Devices.Boiler.Name: Boiler
items.Devices.Bow Turret.Description: This uses bow and arrows to shoot at hostiles. Useful for defending from mobs and biters.
items.Devices.Bow Turret.Name: Bow Turret
items.Devices.Cargo Ejector.Description: This is used to send cargo to a cargo pad. Useful for sending items from a spaceship to a planet. This can only be placed on spaceships.
items.Devices.Cargo Ejector.Name: Cargo Ejector
items.Devices.Cargo Pad.Description: Can recieve cargo from space ships using a cargo ejector! This can be placed on both planets and spaceships.
items.Devices.Cargo Pad.Name: Cargo Pad
items.Devices.Centrifuge.Description: Extracts uranium 235 & 238 from uranium ore. With Uranium Reprocessing unlocked you may also refuel Uranium Fuel cells using 8 u238 here. And you can enrich uranium by using one u235 with eight u238!
items.Devices.Centrifuge.Name: Centrifuge
items.Devices.Chunk Loader.Description: This device can load chunks around it. The radius of chunks is configurable. The higher the radius the more power needed!
items.Devices.Chunk Loader.Name: Chunk Loader
items.Devices.Cold Fusion Reactor.Description: Generates power from cold fusion, the ultimate power source. This is intended to be debug item.
items.Devices.Cold Fusion Reactor.Name: Cold Fusion Reactor
items.Devices.Combustion Generator.Description: Produces a steady power supply from burning fuel items. Fuel will burn twice as long compared to vanilla.
items.Devices.Combustion Generator.Name: Combustion Generator
items.Devices.Crafter.Description: This is useful for crafting items crafted in a crafting table. This attempts to craft the item in the craft slot using resources from its input slots. It will output crafted items into its output slots.
items.Devices.Crafter.Name: Crafter
items.Devices.Crank Generator.Description: Cranking this up or down will generate a small amount of power in exchange for your hunger.
items.Devices.Crank Generator.Name: Crank Generator
items.Devices.Crude Assembler.Description: Unlike most devices, this one doesn't use power. It crafts items very slowly. It attempts to craft the selected item and uses resources from its input slots to craft. It will output crafted items into its output slots.
items.Devices.Crude Assembler.Name: Crude Assembler
items.Devices.Crusher.Description: Can crush various materials for various results. You can crush most stones for gravel and gravel can be crushed further for sand. You can also crush logs, bone blocks or 8 sticks for one charcoal.
items.Devices.Crusher.Name: Crusher
items.Devices.Deep Drill.Description: This requires iron pickaxes or better to work. Requiures lubricant to work from liquid pipes. Resources collected are based on the resource zone this is placed in. Can also deep drill oil at an effecient rate!
items.Devices.Deep Drill.Name: Deep Drill
items.Devices.Electric Blast Furnace.Descripti: Uses electricity from the connected power grid to smelt items. Behaves like a normal blast furnace otherwise.
items.Devices.Electric Blast Furnace.Name: Electric Blast Furnace
items.Devices.Electric Furnace.Description: Uses electricity to smelt items instead of fuel. Behaves like a normal furnace otherwise.
items.Devices.Electric Furnace.Name: Electric Furnace
items.Devices.Electric Smoker.Description: This device uses power from the connected power grid to cook foods instead of fuel. Otherwise this operates like a normal smoker.
items.Devices.Electric Smoker.Name: Electric Smoker
items.Devices.Elevator.Description: Swapping items (f) while standing and looking up or down on this device will activate it. This device can teleport you up to 20 blocks to another elevator on the same x and z coordinates.
items.Devices.Elevator.Name: Elevator
items.Devices.Experience Synthesizer.Descripti: Extracts experience from input items. Uses glass bottles to create experience bottles. Some items give more experience then others like lapis and most mob drops.
items.Devices.Experience Synthesizer.Name: Experience Synthesizer
items.Devices.Exporter.Description: This device is used to export goods in return for money.
items.Devices.Exporter.Name: Exporter
items.Devices.Flood Light.Description: Covers a massive area with light. Light can only be created in air spaces though. This will also only work when powered.
items.Devices.Flood Light.Name: Flood Light
items.Devices.Gas Extractor.Description: This extracts gases from the planets atmosphere. The planet can change the speed at which the gas fills though. And some planets might not even have an atmosphere.
items.Devices.Gas Extractor.Name: Gas Extractor
items.Devices.Geothermal Generator.Description: This needs lava around it to work, as well as a cut copper slab above it for the best output. Waxed copper is best because the oxidation reduces power output.
items.Devices.Geothermal Generator.Name: Geothermal Generator
items.Devices.Glowstone Generator.Description: This burns glowstone to generate power. It burns 2x longer in the nether. Produce nether items when consuming glowstone.
items.Devices.Glowstone Generator.Name: Glowstone Generator
items.Devices.Heat Exchanger.Description: Uses heat from an adjacent nuclear reactor to produce steam. Requires water from a liquid pipeline.
items.Devices.Heat Exchanger.Name: Heat Exchanger
items.Devices.Heavy Steam Generator.Descriptio: This device uses steam from a liquid pipe connection to generate power. It uses alot more steam then a normal steam engine, this is intended to be used with a nuclear reactor setup but it could be used with boilers.
items.Devices.Heavy Steam Generator.Name: Heavy Steam Generator
items.Devices.Human Teleporter.Description: Teleports players to another human teleporter. These are linked via the wire tool! Has a max range of 300 blocks.
items.Devices.Human Teleporter.Name: Human Teleporter
items.Devices.Hydrogen Engine.Description: Uses hydrogen cansiters to produce power. Empty canisters will be returned!
items.Devices.Hydrogen Engine.Name: Hydrogen Engine
items.Devices.Importer.Description: This device is used to buy goods using money from exporter devices.
items.Devices.Importer.Name: Importer
items.Devices.Incinerator.Description: This device will delete any items that are placed into its input slots.
items.Devices.Incinerator.Name: Incinerator
items.Devices.Infuser.Description: Infusing has a chance to destroy its inputs. Can turn sand into redstone. Redsand has a better success rate. Can turn spider eyes into ender eyes! When using amethyst shards items always infuse.
items.Devices.Infuser.Name: Infuser
items.Devices.Item Forge.Description: This device creates the target item from nothing. This is intended to be a debug item.
items.Devices.Item Forge.Name: Item Forge
items.Devices.Item Teleporter.Description: Teleports items from on item teleporter to another. These can be linked using the wire tool. The further the distance the more power used. The distance is capped at 32 blocks.
items.Devices.Item Teleporter.Name: Item Teleporter
items.Devices.Laser Turret.Description: This turret uses energy from the connected power grid to shoot. Useful for defending from mobs and biters.
items.Devices.Laser Turret.Name: Laser Turret
items.Devices.Lightning Generator.Description: Needs clear sky access, this can only be struck during storms. Higher placement will increase the strike chance. This will produce a lot of power when struck.
items.Devices.Lightning Generator.Name: Lightning Generator
items.Devices.Liquid Silo.Description: This does not require power to output liquids. And it can only store one liquid at a time. However it has a large capacity for liquids.
items.Devices.Liquid Silo.Name: Liquid Silo
items.Devices.Mine Layer.Description: Scatters land mines evenly in a 9x9 area in front of the device. Landmines need to placed in the devices input slots.
items.Devices.Mine Layer.Name: Mine Layer
items.Devices.Mob Blocker.Description: This device prevents hostile mobs from spawning naturally nearby. This will not stop spawners, biters or other non natural spawns.
items.Devices.Mob Blocker.Name: Mob Blocker
items.Devices.Moonlight Panel.Description: Produces power so long as it has clear sky access. Creates the most power during midnight. The moon cycle greatly effects power output. Also effected by cloud coverage. However you can bypass this by building above the clouds!
items.Devices.Moonlight Panel.Name: Moonlight Panel
items.Devices.Mover.Description: Used to move items from containers and devices. Can be upgraded in various ways once placed, noteably it can be used to make conveyor belts from carpet starting from the direction its facing!
items.Devices.Mover.Name: Mover
items.Devices.Nuclear Reactor.Description: Requires water from a liquid pipeline to keep the reactor cool. Transfers heat to adjacent heat exchangers. Requires Uranium Fuel Cells to run.
items.Devices.Nuclear Reactor.Name: Nuclear Reactor
items.Devices.Observatory.Description: Produces space science packs. Requires spy glasses to produce. This run 100x slower on planets.
items.Devices.Observatory.Name: Observatory
items.Devices.Oil Refinery.Description: Used to convert items and liquids into various liquids. This requires a liquid pipes to transport liquids into it. It also outputs liquids which can be used by liquids pipes as well.
items.Devices.Oil Refinery.Name: Oil Refinery
items.Devices.Overdriver.Description: This can overdrive movers to make them faster. It can also overdrive devices, which will make them perform their action an additional time but also it will consume more power as a result.
items.Devices.Overdriver.Name: Overdriver
items.Devices.Petroleum Engine.Description: Uses petroleum to generate power. Requires grindstones on the left and right side of the device for full efficiency. Petroleum needs to be piped in using liquid pipes.
items.Devices.Petroleum Engine.Name: Petroleum Engine
items.Devices.Phase Relay.Description: Used with a Phase Beacon. Which can return the player to a linked phase relay!
items.Devices.Phase Relay.Name: Phase Relay
items.Devices.Pollution Deleter.Description: This device sets the superchunks pollution to zero! This is intended to be debug item.
items.Devices.Pollution Deleter.Name: Pollution Deleter
items.Devices.Pollution Generator.Description: Generates a large amount of pollution from nothing. This is intended to be a debug item.
items.Devices.Pollution Generator.Name: Pollution Generator
items.Devices.Power Breaker.Description: Connects to multiple devices. It will mirror its on / off state to the connected devices. It will turn off when exceeding a specified power level.
items.Devices.Power Breaker.Name: Power Breaker
items.Devices.Power Meter.Description: This device can be linked to another device to track its power production or usage.
items.Devices.Power Meter.Name: Power Meter
items.Devices.Power Provider.Description: This device is used to provide power to other power receivers for a set price.
items.Devices.Power Provider.Name: Power Provider
items.Devices.Power Pylon Mk2.Description: All devices can connect to this device. This device can connect to other power pylons from further away.
items.Devices.Power Pylon Mk2.Name: Power Pylon Mk2
items.Devices.Power Pylon.Description: All devices can connect to this device. This device can connect to other power pylons from further away.
items.Devices.Power Pylon.Name: Power Pylon
items.Devices.Power Receiver.Description: This works like a battery device. It can only be charged from Power Transmitters.
items.Devices.Power Receiver.Name: Power Receiver
items.Devices.Power Substation.Description: This is like a power pylon however it has a configurable power range instead!
items.Devices.Power Substation.Name: Power Substation
items.Devices.Power Transmitter.Description: This device links to a power reciever. It send a configurable amount of power to the reciever. The further the distance the more power that is needed to send the desired power. Batteries always discharge first on a power grid. So this will only be used if its needed.
items.Devices.Power Transmitter.Name: Power Transmitter
items.Devices.Production Monitor.Description: This displays production stats! These stats are limited to the power grid the device is a part of.
items.Devices.Production Monitor.Name: Production Monitor
items.Devices.Provider Chest.Description: This device can provide items to a requester chests requests. Logistic Robots will pick up items from this.
items.Devices.Provider Chest.Name: Provider Chest
items.Devices.Pump.Description: This pulls liquids from beneath it. It then outputs the liquid into connected liquid pipes. It can extract oil from oil fields so long as it has a solid block beneath it. Needs a body of water of 25 blocks to output at full effcicieny.
items.Devices.Pump.Name: Pump
items.Devices.Rail Gun.Description: This can destroy incoming asteroids in one hit. It has a limited firing arc of 10 blocks in the direction its facing. It wont fire if the target is within 10 blocks of it.
items.Devices.Rail Gun.Name: Rail Gun
items.Devices.Redstone Emitter.Description: This device is linked to redstone. Which will power redstone if the device is powered. Device power depends on distance to connected redstone. And it can have multiple connections.
items.Devices.Redstone Emitter.Name: Redstone Emitter
items.Devices.Requester Chest.Description: This device can place requests to the logistic network. It uses the top row of items as the request. Logistic Robots will drop off items to this.
items.Devices.Requester Chest.Name: Requester Chest
items.Devices.Research Lab.Description: This device is uses to research technology! It converts science packs into technology progress!
items.Devices.Research Lab.Name: Research Lab
items.Devices.Roboport.Description: This device supplies logistic robots to the network. These robots will move the items from provider chests to requester chests.
items.Devices.Roboport.Name: Roboport
items.Devices.Rocket Silo.Description: The pinnacle of engineering. This devie can be used to send rockets into space. It also is used to make spaceships. It requires a 5x5 launch pad of solid blocks directly above it.
items.Devices.Rocket Silo.Name: Rocket Silo
items.Devices.SAM Site.Description: This will shoot down incoming meteors, asteroids or phantoms if enabled. It uses SAM ammo to do so.
items.Devices.SAM Site.Name: SAM Site
items.Devices.Ship Core.Description: The heart of any spaceship. This needs to be placed into a rocket silo in order to create a space ship!
items.Devices.Ship Core.Name: Ship Core
items.Devices.Sifter.Description: Sifts through various materials for trace items. Sand, dirt, soul sand and soul soil can be sifted for trace materials. Sand is notable for having trace amounts of iron and gold.
items.Devices.Sifter.Name: Sifter
items.Devices.Solar Panel.Description: Produces power so long as it has clear sky access. Creates the most power during mid day. Is also effected by cloud coverage. However you can bypass this by building above the clouds!
items.Devices.Solar Panel.Name: Solar Panel
items.Devices.Steam Engine.Description: Uses steam to generate power. Requires grindstones on the left and right side of the device for full efficiency. Steam needs to be piped in using liquid pipes.
items.Devices.Steam Engine.Name: Steam Engine
items.Devices.Thruster.Description: This is used to propel connected spaceships using gas connsters filled with hydrogen. This will always face south when placed. This will damage and break blocks in the south direction in a 3x3x10 area!
items.Devices.Thruster.Name: Thruster
items.Devices.Tidal Generator.Description: Place iron trapdoors on the left and right side of this for max effcicieny. Generates the most power at midnight and midday! Works best in ocean biomes! Rivers are okay!
items.Devices.Tidal Generator.Name: Tidal Generator
items.Devices.Trade Beacon.Description: You can only have one of these placed at a time. This device can detect trade ships in orbit. Which you can trade with once detected. Detections happen every 30-45 minutes. They only stay in orbit for 5-10 minutes.
items.Devices.Trade Beacon.Name: Trade Beacon
items.Devices.Train Station.Description: Uses locomotives to move mass amounts of items from one station to another. This moves items in stacks rather then 1 by 1.
items.Devices.Train Station.Name: Train Station
items.Devices.Wind Turbine.Description: This device works best in an open area and works better the higher up it is. It also doesn't perform well when other turbines are to close.
items.Devices.Wind Turbine.Name: Wind Turbine
items.Items.Advanced Circuit.Description: This is used for more complex devices and recipes.
items.Items.Advanced Circuit.Name: Advanced Circuit
items.Items.Artillery Beacon.Description: This is used to signal to nearby Artillery Devices to fire a payload at the hit location.
items.Items.Artillery Beacon.Name: Artillery Beacon
items.Items.Artillery Shell.Description: This shell is shot from the Artillery Device.
items.Items.Artillery Shell.Name: Artillery Shell
items.Items.Auto Bow.Description: This bow shoots 2 additional arrows when shot.
items.Items.Auto Bow.Name: Auto Bow
items.Items.Automation Science Pack.Descriptio: A basic science pack used for researching new technologies! It can be used at a research lab.
items.Items.Automation Science Pack.Name: Automation Science Pack
items.Items.Blast Charge.Description: This is used by a blast pickaxe. Its useful for mining a large area quickly.
items.Items.Blast Charge.Name: Blast Charge
items.Items.Burst Bow.Description: This bow is like a shotgun, but for bows. It shoots multiple arrows in a cone after shooting it.
items.Items.Burst Bow.Name: Burst Bow
items.Items.Chemical Science Pack.Description: A science pack used for more advanced research! It can be used at a research lab.
items.Items.Chemical Science Pack.Name: Chemical Science Pack
items.Items.Cliff Explosive.Description: This explosive will destroy a large amount of blocks. However it has a better chance of leaving ores behind.
items.Items.Cliff Explosive.Name: Cliff Explosive
items.Items.Copper Cable.Description: A cabe made of copper. This is used in many crafts.
items.Items.Copper Cable.Name: Copper Cable
items.Items.Copper Plate.Description: A plate of copper. Used in many crafts.
items.Items.Copper Plate.Name: Copper Plate
items.Items.EVA Module.Description: Allows power armor to act as a space suit and oxygen mask!
items.Items.EVA Module.Name: EVA Module
items.Items.Electric Engine Unit.Description: These are similar to Engine Units, though these are typically used in advanced proudcts.
items.Items.Electric Engine Unit.Name: Electric Engine Unit
items.Items.Electronic Circuit.Description: You can never have enough of these! Most devices use these in their crafting recipes!
items.Items.Electronic Circuit.Name: Electronic Circuit
items.Items.Empty Gas Canister.Description: This can be filled with gas from a gas extractor.
items.Items.Empty Gas Canister.Name: Empty Gas Canister
items.Items.Engine Unit.Description: These are very iron dense components. Used commonly in intermediate products.
items.Items.Engine Unit.Name: Engine Unit
items.Items.Exoskeleton.Description: This gives a speed buff when worn! However it only works if the player is in range of a powergrid. Which it will consume 10 power from the grid.
items.Items.Exoskeleton.Name: Exoskeleton
items.Items.Explosive Crossbow.Description: This bow shoots arrows with grenades on the other end of it. It needs both arrows and grenades to work fully.
items.Items.Explosive Crossbow.Name: Explosive Crossbow
items.Items.Explosive.Description: This is used to make cliff explosives.
items.Items.Explosive.Name: Explosive
items.Items.Flint Powder.Description: This is made from flint. A common industrial biproduct. This is noteably used to make gunpowder.
items.Items.Flint Powder.Name: Flint Powder
items.Items.Flying Robot Frame.Description: This is used to craft logistic robots. Which can be used to move items all over a factory freely.
items.Items.Flying Robot Frame.Name: Flying Robot Frame
items.Items.Gas Canister.Description: A special canister that can store 100 units of any gas.
items.Items.Gas Canister.Name: Gas Canister
items.Items.Grenade.Description: This can be used to explode a small area. It does a good amount of damage to mobs to.
items.Items.Grenade.Name: Grenade
items.Items.Integrated Exoskeleton.Description: Allows power armor to increase the speed of the wearer.
items.Items.Integrated Exoskeleton.Name: Integrated Exoskeleton
items.Items.Iron Gear Wheel.Description: A simple gear used in a fair amount of recipes.
items.Items.Iron Gear Wheel.Name: Iron Gear Wheel
items.Items.Iron Plate.Description: A plate of iron. This is used in many crafts.
items.Items.Iron Plate.Name: Iron Plate
items.Items.Land Mine.Description: This will explode when hostile are near. This can be placed automatically by a Mine Placer.
items.Items.Land Mine.Name: Land Mine
items.Items.Liquid Barrel.Description: This is used to store liquids! Use a barrel pump to empty or fill it!
items.Items.Liquid Barrel.Name: Liquid Barrel
items.Items.Locomotive.Description: Place inside a train station, which can then be used to move items vast distances.
items.Items.Locomotive.Name: Locomotive
items.Items.Logistic Robot.Description: Place this in a roboport! This is used to move items around a factory using requester chests and provider chests!
items.Items.Logistic Robot.Name: Logistic Robot
items.Items.Logistic Science Pack.Description: A basic science pack used for researching many breakthrough technologies! It can be used at a research lab.
items.Items.Logistic Science Pack.Name: Logistic Science Pack
items.Items.Low Density Structure.Description: A high end component, not used in many things but very expensive.
items.Items.Low Density Structure.Name: Low Density Structure
items.Items.Micro Battery.Description: An advanced crafting ingredient. Used in flying robot frames.
items.Items.Micro Battery.Name: Micro Battery
items.Items.Military Science Pack.Description: A science pack used for researching new military technologies! It can be used at a research lab.
items.Items.Military Science Pack.Name: Military Science Pack
items.Items.Mobile Battery.Description: Allows power armor to store power so that it works off a power grid. Adds 1k power storage.
items.Items.Mobile Battery.Name: Mobile Battery
items.Items.Mobile Solar Panel.Description: Allows power armor to generate a trickle of power when exposed to sunlight.
items.Items.Mobile Solar Panel.Name: Mobile Solar Panel
items.Items.Modular Power Armor Mk2.Descriptio: Uses modular power chips from the top row of the wearers inventory when powered by a power grid or from a mobile battery.
items.Items.Modular Power Armor Mk2.Name: Modular Power Armor Mk2
items.Items.Modular Power Armor.Description: Uses modular power chips from the top row of the wearers inventory when powered by a power grid or from a mobile battery.
items.Items.Modular Power Armor.Name: Modular Power Armor
items.Items.Mover Gear.Description: Can be added to a placed mover by right clicking the mover with this in your hand. This will allow the mover to move 2 more items at a time. This doesnt do anything for motorized movers.
items.Items.Mover Gear.Name: Mover Gear
items.Items.Oxygen Mask.Description: Can use oxygen tanks to provide oxygen to the wearer. Can also be used to breath in low oxygen enviroments (0.75 or Higher) without an oxygen tank.
items.Items.Oxygen Mask.Name: Oxygen Mask
items.Items.Oxygen Tank.Description: Can provude oxygen to other items while in the top row of your inventory.
items.Items.Oxygen Tank.Name: Oxygen Tank
items.Items.Personal Laser Turret.Description: Allows power armor to shoot a laser at nearby enemies.
items.Items.Personal Laser Turret.Name: Personal Laser Turret
items.Items.Personal Shield Generator.Descript: Allows power armor to deflect any type of damage. So long as the power armor is powered.
items.Items.Personal Shield Generator.Name: Personal Shield Generator
items.Items.Phase Beacon.Description: Will link to a Phase Relay on any ship when you board it. Then you can right click this and you will be teleported to the phase relay. This will only work with the Phase Relay if it has a full charge!
items.Items.Phase Beacon.Name: Phase Beacon
items.Items.Pipe Tool.Description: An engineers second best friend. This can show liquid connections and the flow of liquid.
items.Items.Pipe Tool.Name: Pipe Tool
items.Items.Plastic Bar.Description: Made from petroleum this common ingredient is used for intermediate products.
items.Items.Plastic Bar.Name: Plastic Bar
items.Items.Portable Crafter.Description: You can right click this while holding it to open a crafting table! You can also use /mt craft, as well!
items.Items.Portable Crafter.Name: Portable Crafter
items.Items.Processing Unit.Description: These are used in the most advanced recipes.
items.Items.Processing Unit.Name: Processing Unit
items.Items.Production Science Pack.Descriptio: A science pack specifically for production! It can be used at a research lab.
items.Items.Production Science Pack.Name: Production Science Pack
items.Items.Railgun Round.Description: Used by the Railgun device to decimiate incoming objects.
items.Items.Railgun Round.Name: Railgun Round
items.Items.Repair Pack.Description: This is used to repair damaged blocks that biters have attacked.
items.Items.Repair Pack.Name: Repair Pack
items.Items.Rocket Fuel.Description: A dense fuel used to launch rockets at a rocket silo.
items.Items.Rocket Fuel.Name: Rocket Fuel
items.Items.Rocket Parts.Description: These are used to launch rockets at a rocket silo.
items.Items.Rocket Parts.Name: Rocket Parts
items.Items.SAM Missile.Description: Used by SAM sites to shoot incoming objects.
items.Items.SAM Missile.Name: SAM Missile
items.Items.Seismic Charge.Description: This item is used to find resource zones. Which can be mined by a deep drill.
items.Items.Seismic Charge.Name: Seismic Charge
items.Items.Solid Fuel.Description: A burnable fuel source. Its like a coal block for furnaces and can be used by locomotives for fuel. It's also used for rocket fuel.
items.Items.Solid Fuel.Name: Solid Fuel
items.Items.Space Science Pack.Description: A rare science pack used for unlocking legendary technologies! It can be used at a research lab.
items.Items.Space Science Pack.Name: Space Science Pack
items.Items.Space Suit.Description: Protects the wearer in extreme temperatures from 0.5 - 2.0, anything outside this range will only be mitigated.
items.Items.Space Suit.Name: Space Suit
items.Items.Steel Plate.Description: A common ingredient for intermediate to advanced crafts.
items.Items.Steel Plate.Name: Steel Plate
items.Items.Sulfur.Description: Very smelly, but very useful. This can be converted into sulfuric acid, which is useful for mining uranium.
items.Items.Sulfur.Name: Sulfur
items.Items.Thermometer.Description: Right click to get the temperature at your location. Yseful for diagnosing temperature.
items.Items.Thermometer.Name: Thermometer
items.Items.Tunnel Pickaxe.Description: This pickaxe can be used to make 3x3x3 tunnels! Uses blast charges from your inventory. Works as a normal pickaxe otherwise.
items.Items.Tunnel Pickaxe.Name: Tunnel Pickaxe
items.Items.Uranium 235.Description: This is the uranium used to craft Uranium Fuel Cells. It's much more rare then u238.
items.Items.Uranium 235.Name: Uranium 235
items.Items.Uranium 238.Description: A common form of uranium. This is used with Uranium Reprocessing and uranium enrichment to make u235.
items.Items.Uranium 238.Name: Uranium 238
items.Items.Uranium Fuel Cell.Description: This can be used to power a nuclear reactor.
items.Items.Uranium Fuel Cell.Name: Uranium Fuel Cell
items.Items.Uranium Ore.Description: This ore can be processed in a Centrifuge. Which breaks down into u235 and u238.
items.Items.Uranium Ore.Name: Uranium Ore
items.Items.Used Uranium Fuel Cell.Description: This can be used in a Centrifuge to be refueled.
items.Items.Used Uranium Fuel Cell.Name: Used Uranium Fuel Cell
items.Items.Utility Science Pack.Description: A science pack used for many technologies! It can be used at a research lab.
items.Items.Utility Science Pack.Name: Utility Science Pack
items.Items.Wire Tool.Description: An engineers best friend. This is used for many things.
items.Items.Wire Tool.Name: Wire Tool

tech.Technologies.Advanced Assembly.Descripti: A major technological breakthrough! Unlocks the Advanced Assembler, critical for crafting complex devices and items.
tech.Technologies.Advanced Bow Technology.Des: Unlocks the auto bow and the burst bow!
tech.Technologies.Advanced Bow Turrets.Descri: Unlocks a better turret that can defend your factory!
tech.Technologies.Advanced Circuits.Descripti: Unlocks the crafting of Advanced Circuits, used in complex recipes.
tech.Technologies.Advanced Furnaces.Descripti: Unlocks the Electric Blast Furnace and Electric Smoker.
tech.Technologies.Artillery.Description: This unlocks a device that can launch artillery shells up to 500 blocks away using artillery beacons.
tech.Technologies.Asteroid Mining.Description: This unlocks a way to gather resources from asteroids in space!
tech.Technologies.Automated Collecting.Descri: Unlocks the auto collector! This allows for drops to be collected! The auto collector is great for vanilla farms.
tech.Technologies.Automated Farming.Descripti: Unlocks the auto harvester and auto planter! Critical for automating crops!
tech.Technologies.Automated Husbandry.Descrip: Unlocks various devices for automating husbandry.
tech.Technologies.Automated Mines.Description: This device scatters landmines evenly in front of it!
tech.Technologies.Basic Power Management.Desc: Unlocks the battery monitor for toggling on and off devices, also unlocks the power meter!
tech.Technologies.Basic Power Storage.Descrip: Unlocks the ability to store power!
tech.Technologies.Basic Refinement.Descriptio: Unlocks devices that crush down stone and sift sand for valuable resources. Useful for finding iron and gold.
tech.Technologies.Blueprinter.Description: This device allows you to create blueprint cards which can be used to build a selection of blocks anywhere else automatically! Like schematics!
tech.Technologies.Chunk Loading.Description: This device unlocks the chunk loader which uses a lot of power to keep chunks loaded.
tech.Technologies.Cliff Explosives.Descriptio: An explosive that is much stronger than TNT.
tech.Technologies.Deep Drilling.Description: Deep drilling can harvest specific raw resources from resource zones found via seismic charges.
tech.Technologies.EVA Module.Description: This unlocks a module that acts like an oxygen mask and a space suit! Making the modular power armor even better!
tech.Technologies.Electric Engines.Descriptio: Unlocks the Electric Engine Unit recipe! Used for advanced technology!
tech.Technologies.Electric Smelting.Descripti: This device uses power to smelt resources instead of coal!
tech.Technologies.Environmental Protection.De: This unlocks a way to fight extreme temperatures and provide oxygen in no oxygen areas!
tech.Technologies.Environmental Stability.Des: This unlocks tecnology that can be used to stabliize the heat and oxygen in an enclosed space. Useful for spaceships and for hazardous planets.
tech.Technologies.Example.Description: This will not show up in the tech tree, its purely for reference.
tech.Technologies.Example.Perm Text: Rocket Engineer or Whatever you want
tech.Technologies.Exoskeleton Equipment.Descr: Unlocks the Exoskeleton! This speeds the user up when in power grid range!
tech.Technologies.Experience Extraction.Descr: Unlocks the Experience Synthesizer, which can extract a small amount of experience from most items.
tech.Technologies.Explosive Crossbow Technolo: Unlocks the auto bow and the burst bow!
tech.Technologies.Flint Powder.Description: Unlocks the ability to craft Flint Powder from Flint. Flint Powder can then be used to create Gunpowder.
tech.Technologies.Gas Extraction.Description: Unlocks the Gas Extractor device, which can extract gases from a planets atmosphere. This will also unlock the gas canister!
tech.Technologies.Geothermal Harvesting.Descr: Harvest power from lava using the unlocked device!
tech.Technologies.Glowstone Power.Description: Harvest a unique power source, glowstone!
tech.Technologies.Human Teleporting.Descripti: This device uses power to teleport players long distances.
tech.Technologies.Human Transport.Description: Unlocks the Elevator device. Which can teleport players up and down.
tech.Technologies.Hydrogen Power.Description: Unlocks the hydrogen generator. This device uses hydrogen supplied via gas cansiters to produce power!
tech.Technologies.Integerated Exoskeleton.Des: Unlocks the Integrated Exoskeleton power armor chip! This chip allows the wearer to move at a faster speed.
tech.Technologies.Item Infuser.Description: Unlocks the Infuser device, this device can infuse some items.
tech.Technologies.Item Teleporter.Description: Unlocks the Item Teleporter device. Which can teleport items to other teleporters!
tech.Technologies.Land Mines.Description: Unlocks land mines! These are great for defense!
tech.Technologies.Laser Turret.Description: Unlocks a laser turret to defend your factory!
tech.Technologies.Laser Upgrades.Description: Your laser weapons deal 50% more damage.
tech.Technologies.Lightning Harvesting.Descri: Harvest power from lightning strikes! Unlocks a device that works well in stormy areas!
tech.Technologies.Liquid Storage.Description: Store liquids inside of liquid silo!
tech.Technologies.Liquid Transport.Descriptio: Unlocks the Barrel Pump & Pump device. Which can unload and load liquids into barrels.
tech.Technologies.Locomotive Technology.Descr: Unlocks Train Stations and Locomotives, critical for long-range resource transport.
tech.Technologies.Logging Technology.Descript: Unlock a device to chop down trees!
tech.Technologies.Logistic Robot Speed.Descri: Your logistic robots now more 2x faster!
tech.Technologies.Logistic Robots.Description: Unlock logistic robots, provider chests, requester chests and roboports!
tech.Technologies.Low Density Structure.Descr: Unlocks Low Density Structure! This is vital in progressing technology and reaching space!
tech.Technologies.Micro Battery Technology.De: Unlock a small battery that can be used to power remote devices.
tech.Technologies.Military Science.Descriptio: Unlocks acess to military tech science pack!
tech.Technologies.Mob Blocker.Description: This unlocks a device that prevents hostile mobs from naturally spawning in a 100 block radius around it.
tech.Technologies.Mobile Power.Description: Unlocks the Mobile Battery and Mobile Solar Panel power armor chip! This allows the wearer to store power so that they can use the power armor while off the power grid.
tech.Technologies.Modular Power Armor.Descrip: Unlocks the modular power armor, these industrial items can use modular power chips to allow the wearer to have advanced abilities.
tech.Technologies.Mover Gears.Description: Unlocks mover gears which can be added to mover to increase the amount of items they can move when interacting with containers, not belts.
tech.Technologies.Observation.Description: The observatory is used to generate space science, it is 100x slower on planets compared to in space!
tech.Technologies.Oil Technology.Description: Unlocks the Oil Refinery, a critical device for technological progression. Also unlocks Solid Fuel recipes.
tech.Technologies.Overdriving.Description: The Overdriver is a device that can double, triple, or even quadruple the speed of devices!
tech.Technologies.Personal Energy Shield.Desc: Unlocks the Personal Shield Generator power armor chip This chip allows the wearer to avoid damage from any source if they have enough stored power!
tech.Technologies.Personal Turret.Description: Unlocks the Personal Laser Turret power armor chip! This chip allows the wearer to shoot a laser at nearby hostile mobs.
tech.Technologies.Petrol Power.Description: Unlocks petroleum power! An incredible source of power.
tech.Technologies.Phase Technology.Descriptio: This gives you a practical way to get up to a spaceship and down to a planet.
tech.Technologies.Placer Technology.Descripti: Unlock the auto placer which is used place blocks in a rectangle! Useful for making flat factory areas or walls!
tech.Technologies.Power Transmission I.Descri: Unlock the mark two power pylon, this pylon has a 50% increase in its power range.
tech.Technologies.Power Transmission II.Descr: This unlocks a device that can have its grid range changed!
tech.Technologies.Processing Units.Descriptio: Unlocks the Processing Unit recipe! Used for advanced technology!
tech.Technologies.Quarry Technology.Descripti: Unlock the autominer, used for mining out large areas.
tech.Technologies.Railgun Technology.Descript: Unlocks the rail gun! A Power spaceship weapon that can destroy asteroids in one hit!
tech.Technologies.Research Efficiency I.Descr: Your research labs now research faster.
tech.Technologies.Research Efficiency II.Desc: Your research labs now research even faster.
tech.Technologies.Research Efficiency III.Des: Your research labs now research much faster.
tech.Technologies.Rocket Silo.Description: A rocket silo that can launch rockets into space. A technological feat in itself.
tech.Technologies.SAM Technology.Description: Unlocks the SAM Site & SAM Missiles, these are used to shoot down incoming meteors, phantoms and to shoot incoming small asteroids in space.
tech.Technologies.Seismic Reading.Description: This item can be used to determine a chunk’s resource potential, such as oil chunks or hidden resource deposits for deep drilling!
tech.Technologies.Solar Cleaning.Description: Uses a brush to clean off nearby solar panels!!
tech.Technologies.Solar Harvesting.Descriptio: Unlocks ways to harness power from the sun and indirectly from the sun.
tech.Technologies.Space Travel.Description: The sky is no longer the limit. It's time to go beyond it!
tech.Technologies.Steam Technology.Descriptio: A major power breakthrough! Unlocks steam engines and boilers!
tech.Technologies.Tidal Harvesting.Descriptio: Harvest power from water using the unlocked device!
tech.Technologies.Timings Technology.Descript: Unlock the autotimer which is used to send redstone signals on a timer! Also required for some other automated technology.
tech.Technologies.Tunnel Pickaxe.Description: Unlock the tunnel pickaxe and the blast charge! These can be used together for making classic 3x3 tunnels.
tech.Technologies.Uranium Reprocessing.Descri: Unlocks the ability to recycle used fuel cells and enrich uranium 238 using uranium 235.
tech.Technologies.Utility Science.Description: Used in most utility and advanced technology!
tech.Technologies.Warning System.Description: Unlocks the biter detector! Useful for detecting attacks before they strike!
tech.Technologies.Waste Disposal.Description: Unlocks the incinerator. Which vaporizes items at the cost of pollution.
tech.Technologies.Wind Harvesting.Description: Harvest power from wind using the unlocked device!
tech.Technologies.Wireless Power.Description: The unlocks two devices that allow you to send and recieve power wirelessly.
tech.Technologies.Wireless Redstone.Descripti: The unlocks a device to transmit power wirelessly.
